WsFilter calls WsServerContainer.findMapping("/foo/a/a/bar"), which in turn calls new UriTemplate(path). If the path contains repeated segments, it causes the following code in the UriTemplate constructor to throw an exception:

Segment old =
        this.segments.put(segment, new Segment(index, segment));
if (old != null) {
    throw new IllegalArgumentException(
            sm.getString("uriTemplate.duplicateName", segment));
}

This would be valid if the duplicates were URI variable names but not when their plain path segments.
